Each step adds apparent authority while stripping the previous step’s stated limitations. By the time the claim reaches a legal brief or legislative hearing, its origin in uncontrolled clinical follow-up samples — acknowledged in Cornell’s own Finding 7 — is no longer visible.

**A direction-of-finding consensus is not a GRADE-quality consensus. Institutional repetition cannot convert low-certainty evidence into settled science.**

